olive oil
1 carrot
1 parsnip
1 beetroot
1 packet flaked almonds
1 packet chicken breast strips
½ pear
1 drizzle balsamic vinegar
1 bag salad leaves
1 sachet Nan's Special Seasoning
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese
1 packet Hollandaise

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Cut carrot, parsnip and beetroot into fries.
• Place veggie fries on a lined oven tray, drizzle
with olive oil and season with salt and pepper.
Toss to coat, spread out evenly, then bake until
tender, 20-25 minutes.

• Meanwhile, heat a large frying pan over
medium-high heat. Toast flaked almonds,
tossing, until golden, 2-3 minutes. Transfer to a
small bowl and set aside.

• In a medium bowl, combine Nan's special
seasoning and a drizzle of olive oil. Add chicken
breast strips and turn to coat.

• Return the frying pan to medium-high heat with
a drizzle of olive oil. Cook chicken until cooked
through, 3-5 minutes each side (cook in batches
if your pan is getting crowded). Transfer to a
plate to rest.

TIP: Chicken is cooked through when it's no longer
pink inside.

• Meanwhile, thinly slice pear (see ingredients).
In a large bowl, combine a drizzle of balsamic
vinegar and olive oil. Season with salt and
pepper.
• Add salad leaves, pear and grated Parmesan
cheese. Toss to coat.

• Divide chicken, rainbow veggie fries and
Parmesan-pear salad between plates.
• Spoon any resting juices over chicken.
Sprinkle over toasted almonds and serve with
Hollandaise. Enjoy!